        <p class="metadata">Posted by Andries Seutens (andries) on 2012-08-01T18:40:25.000+0000</p> 
        <div class="body">
            <p>You must manually cast the value to whatever your database expects. This is not the responsibility of Zend Framework.</p>

<p>For example to cast to an ENUM value "true" or "false", you can do:</p>

<pre class="highlight"><code>
$x = false;
$foo-&gt;createRow(
    array(
       'baz' =&gt; $x ? 'true' : 'false'
    )
);
</code></pre>

<p>Or to cast to an integer:</p>

<pre class="highlight"><code>
$x = false;
$foo-&gt;createRow(
    array(
       'baz' =&gt; (int) $x
    )
);
</code></pre>

<p>Closing this issue.</p>

